cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CG 

This paper deals with the problem of finding large cliques in random graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves a fine spectral analysis of the certificate used in previous works, which involves tools from information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper deals with the symmetries in the eigenspaces of set symmetric matrices, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
